{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 03:51:42.953250", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverall assessment\\n- The fabric’s EBGP control plane is largely healthy: all inter-router links are up, and BGP sessions between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging many prefixes as expected.\\n- A specific anomaly affects reachability to subnet 10.0.1.0/24 (host pc_0_1). That prefix is not present in the fabric’s BGP tables, causing inter-subnet traffic to 10.0.1.x to fail.\\n\\nObserved symptoms and tests\\n- Data plane:\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 (10.0.0.2 → 10.0.1.2) ping fails with “From 10.0.0.1 Destination Net Unreachable,” which is an ICMP error generated by leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1). This indicates leaf_router_0_0 lacks a route to 10.0.1.0/24.\\n  - pc_0_1 → pc_0_0 ping command did not complete in time; given the reverse-path issue, even if transmitted, replies would be blackholed at leaf_router_0_0.\\n- Control plane and routing:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 routing table includes many 10.x/24 BGP routes but is missing 10.0.1.0/24. Hence the ICMP “net unreachable” returned by 10.0.0.1.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 routing table correctly shows 10.0.1.0/24 as directly connected and has a BGP-learned route to 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.1.2, indicating BGP sessions are up and receiving other prefixes.\\n  - On both spines, “show ip bgp 10.0.1.0/24” returns “% Network not in table,” confirming the 10.0.1.0/24 prefix is not advertised into the fabric.\\n  - BGP neighbor summaries show sessions are established on all involved routers (peers up with PfxRcd/Sent), so the control-plane transport is functioning.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- The issue localizes to leaf_router_0_1 (the leaf for 10.0.1.0/24).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 FRR configuration is missing an advertisement for its local subnet. Its running configuration has no “network 10.0.1.0/24” under IPv4 unicast (and no redistribute connected), while leaf_router_0_0 properly includes “network 10.0.0.0/24.”\\n  - As a result, 10.0.1.0/24 is not present in the BGP RIB of leaf_router_0_1 (verified by “% Network not in table” when queried) and is not propagated upstream to spines/super-spine.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_1: the 10.0.1.0/24 prefix (the host subnet for pc_0_1) is not being advertised into BGP (missing “network 10.0.1.0/24” under address-family ipv4 unicast or equivalent redistribution). This prevents all other subnets from learning a route to 10.0.1.0/24, leading to network-unreachable errors at the source leaf.\\n\\nImpact scope\\n- All inter-subnet traffic destined to 10.0.1.0/24 is unreachable from the rest of the fabric.\\n- Traffic from 10.0.1.0/24 toward other subnets may be forwarded out (since leaf_router_0_1 knows routes to others), but return traffic will fail due to missing reverse path (as observed from 10.0.0.0/24)., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0d35e9e5-e977-4bd7-b9b7-755e88fb8709'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
